<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-136-306  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 136 306.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  March 20 1989 n306 p61(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Apple mulls doubling minimum reseller buy.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kinley, Patricia.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Apple Computer Inc may double the minimum purchase requirements ofvalue added resellers (VARs) to $500,000 annually in an effort torecruit and support larger VARs.andP;  Some 70 current VARs unable tomeet the volume requirements would be moved into Apple'sdealer-supported VAR (DS-VAR) program, while the total number ofVARs serviced directly by Apple would increase to 300.andP;  Dealerswould be able to earn $500 per VAR per quarter through Apple'sEarned Investment Program.andP;  Currently Apple's DS-VARs, whichinclude companies marketing desktop publishing systems and healthservices, are clustered in metropolitan markets on the East andWest Coasts.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (marketing).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Topic:     Value-Added ResellersDealers and AgentsVolumeSalesPrice.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Apple's VAR program. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>